TopicTitle: [1.3] IR Sequencer v1.0.3 - Add-On to Infernal Robotics (updated 05/06/2017)

Articles.Content: On a different topic.  I saw a discussion a few posts back about being able to edit an old command without making a new one and deleting the old one.  I can totally see that you'd not want a ton of text fields in that UI, but what about something like double clicking on an existing command (or having an edit button) that pops up a small dialog that has the required text fields?

Would it be possible to extend the action groups available if [action groups extended](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/67235-105dec1615-action-groups-extended-250-action-groups-in-flight-editing-now-kosremotetech/) is installed? This would greatly enhance the flexiblity of the mod. Thanks!

Sequences (at least for now) unlike kOS scripts are unique to a vessel they have been created on, so it is nearly impossible. Even making them editable in VAB was a bit hacky. For example if you have 2 identical .craft files loaded within physics range Sequencer would most likely malfunction, due to part ID clashes.

Actually with recent IR API implementation in kOS it is quite easy to write scripts for IR as long as you have all the servos properly tagged.
